# MailPlatform — Production deploy & restart

When code changes are made that require deployment, **always** end the response with these server instructions (adapt steps if only some services changed).

## Server path

`/opt/email-provider`

## Full update (production)

```bash
cd /opt/email-provider
git pull
pnpm install
pnpm db:generate
pnpm db:migrate
pnpm build
pm2 restart mailplatform-api mailplatform-web mailplatform-worker
```

## PM2 process names

| Service | PM2 name |
|---------|----------|
| API | `mailplatform-api` |
| Web | `mailplatform-web` |
| Worker | `mailplatform-worker` |

## Partial restarts (after targeted fixes)

```bash
# API only
pm2 restart mailplatform-api

# Worker only (inbound email ingest, parsing)
pm2 restart mailplatform-worker

# Web only (UI)
pm2 restart mailplatform-web
```

## Optional maintenance

```bash
# Re-parse stored emails missing body content (from S3/rawMime)
pnpm db:reparse
```

## Notes

- Always run `pnpm db:generate` before build if Prisma schema changed.
- Worker must be restarted after email parsing / ingest changes.
- Check logs: `pm2 logs mailplatform-worker --lines 50`
